#Windows Server 2022 and VirtualBox

#Objective
-Installing VirtualBox 7.2.8 and Windows Server 2022

#Tools used
-Virtual Box
-Windows Server 2022

##Steps
-Installed VirtualBox 7.2.8
-Create a new Virtual Machine (Windows Server 2022)
-Virtual Box 7.2.8, click New and input Virtual Machine New name(Avoid spaces)
-Mount the ISO
-Type- Microsoft Windows
-Version Windows 2022 (64-bit)
-Memory- 4GB
-CPU- 2 Cores
-HDD- 80 GB
-Skip unattended installation to do a Manual setup

#Start the VM and install the software
-Select Windows Server 2022 Standard (Desktop Experience) to get the standard graphical user interface, rather than the command-line Core edition.
-Choose Custom installation
-The files will install and restart automatically
-After the restart, you will be prompted to change your Administrator password
-At the Logon screen, you need to send a Ctrl+Alt+Del to log in. In the VirtualBox menu, click on Input, Keyboard, insert Ctrl+Alt+Del, then enter the password to access the desktop

#Lessons Learnt
-Including attended installation when installing the Virtual Machine will give an error with the software later
-The Software Version you select is important since it affects your user experience




 
